RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHES A LUCKY REBEL broke outwardly from the gate while still being the fastest, grabbed the rail, set the pace, saved ground, urged to gain momentum through the turn, kept the rail closed, was challenged by rival around the quarter pole while battling with that one, another rival passed along the outside, shook the first one and went on to battle with the second challenger, matched strides down the lane was driven hard, and determinedly out finished all the rest. LIGHTENING MO stalked the early leader while being rated just off the pace in the three path, shifted out into the four path in the turn, split horses around the quarter pole, collared the first two at the three-sixteenth pole, was able to get past one of the early leaders, laid right next to the first leader where they battled to the end. Gave a great effort but had to settle for the place spot today. CALLING was mid pack after the break, from in between horses, angled out into the five path after the half mile marker, passed horses going into the turn while gaining momentum with every stride, moved to the rail spot mid turn, saved ground until she had to come off the rail in the stretch as she caught the leader and launched her bid for the win, hooked the leader and was within striking distance, had trouble switching leads and gave out a furlong too early, but was still able to run third. STARSNMOTION settled in the second tier in a stalking position early, was allowed to get shuffled further back while saving ground, was being urged along to close ground, split horses at the top of the lane, took advantage of the long stretch and out grinded the rest but was no threat to the first three. HOT GOLDEN GIRL was off a step slow, stayed far back on the outside, continued to race wide, made one run and was able to out finish tiring rivals. MO SMOKING broke out at the start, traveled wide into the turn, started running at the three eighths pole, ran gamely into and down the stretch, was within striking distance, had a glimmer of hope and then tired. TWO JET broke sharp and vied for the lead early, matched strides with foe through the turn, flattened out in the stretch. ATALANTA ASTERIA never involved.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PIONEER OF MEDINA tracked three wide, pursued under coaxing around the far turn, took aim on the clear leader from the five path in upper stretch, bid along with an outer rival in the final furlong, dueled gamely between horses through the closing stages, and prevailed. MR. WIRELESS bobbled a bit at the start while last away, laid off of the pace four wide, tracked around the far turn, fanned to the six path entering the lane, ranged up to bid for the lead leaving the furlong grounds, battled with a pair of inner game rivals through the closing stages, but was staved off. RUN CLASSIC stalked outside of the clear leader and from the four path around the first turn, vied in the two path with that foe into the far turn, gained an advantage at the seven sixteenths pole, showed the way in the four path entering the lane, drifted in subtly as a pair of outer rivals menaced at the furlong grounds, battled with them through the late stages, but was bested. HOIST THE GOLD set a clear pace in the two path around the first turn, got confronted by a rival at the half mile pole, was headed entering the far turn, sustained pressing position around that bend, but gave way approaching midstretch. TAWNY PORT tracked along the inside, saved ground, shifted out to the four path in upper stretch, and lacked a bid. KING FURY trailed in the four path, fanned to the seven path in upper stretch, and moved up. BIG BLUE LINE tracked two wide and between horses, but only managed to chase entering the lane before fading. HAPPY AMERICAN rated at the rear two wide and between horses, took the far turn in the four path before swinging to the six path entering the lane, but lacked a rally. FARMINGTON ROAD settled far back along the inside, took the far turn in the three path, shifted to the five path in midstretch, and failed to factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO EMMYS set the pace in the two to three paths, shook away from outer rivals after shifting to the eight path at the quarter pole, and drew off with good energy. GENTLE SOUL was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe while put to crowded quarters at the start, trailed along the inside, advanced in the seven path and outside of rivals around the far turn, fanned to the ten path entering the lane, rallied while hanging on his left lead to bid for place at the furlong grounds, gained that position in the closing stages, and held it. ENGLISH TAVERN took a bump from an inner rival leaving the gates, laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, trailed into the far turn, fanned from the five path to the eleven path entering the lane, stayed on down the outer part of the course in the final furlong, and reached show late. BAY STREET MONEY laid off of the pace three wide, chased under urging in the six path and between horses around the far turn, came into the lane in the eight path, grinded away to bid for place along with outer rivals in midstretch, but was outkicked in the final sixteenth. PIXELATE bopped the outer part of the gate with his head while leaving it, stalked in the four path, pursued from the five path around the far turn, but lacked a bid before giving way. TIZ THE BOMB tracked along the inside, but gave way around the far turn. CAVALRY CHARGE broke out and bumped a rival at the start, pressed two wide, then from the four path around the far turn, and weakened between horses through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY MISCHIEVOUS stalked two wide and between horses, pressed inside of the leader approaching the half mile pole,, backed off entering the far turn to switch outside of that one and to the four path leaving the three furlong pole, ranged up to bid in the five path entering the lane, battled through upper stretch, wrestled an advantage at the furlong grounds, and subtly inched ahead late. MIRACLE broke a bit outwardly at the start, moved forward to set the pace in the two path into the first turn, shifted out to the three path entering the backstretch, showed the way from chasers around the far turn, dug in in the four path to resist PRETTY MISCHIEVOUS's bid entering the lane, sparred while getting headed in midstretch, fought on gamely through the final furlong, but did not have enough to regain even terms. HOOSIER PHILLY bobbled before bumping an outer rival at the start, laid off of the pace two wide and between horses while under snug restraint behind foes around the first turn, shifted outside of rivals and to the five path at the three furlong pole, inched closer while fanning to the six path around the far turn, but leveled off entering the lane, and secured show. VAHVA tracked along the inside, tugged down the backstretch to striking range inside of the leaders at the nine sixteenths pole, but failed to sustain that position leaving the half mile pole, chased the leaders while saving ground around the far turn, and yielded. CHOP CHOP was last away, shifted outside of foes, tugged forward four wide around the first turn to press entering the backstretch, but came under urging between horses to keep pace turning in the five path turning for home, and gave way entering the lane. KNOCKYOURSOCKSOFF took a bump from an inner rival at the start, lacked speed three wide, faded around the far turn, and was eased through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANGEL OF EMPIRE settled off of the pace in the two path, gained in the four to five paths and between horses around the far turn, sustained a charge after changing leads between horses at the three sixteenths pole, bid at the furlong grounds along with an inner SUN THUNDER, battled with that foe in the final sixteenth, and edged ahead. SUN THUNDER settled far back two wide, awaited racing room while loaded behind rivals turning for home, found clear sailing two wide and between horses entering the lane, rallied to bid inside of the leaders at the furlong grounds, vied through the closing stages, but was outkicked late. TWO PHIL'S bumped with an inner rival at the start, tracked from midpack two wide, moved forward down the backstretch, split foes to gain show at the three furlong pole, took aim outside of the leading pair turning for home, bid for the lead in the four path entering the lane, led in upper stretch, but met challenges from multiple rivals on either side in midstretch, and yielded leaving the sixteenth pole. TAPIT'S CONQUEST settled off of the pace two wide, shifted out approaching the far turn, advanced in the seven path and outside of foes around that bend, sustained a grinding gain in upper stretch, but leveled off at the furlong grounds. SINGLE RULER lacked speed along the inside, swung from the four path to the eight path entering the lane, and stayed on willingly. HARLOCAP pressed two wide, vied around the far turn with a narrow advantage, but came into the lane in the three path before being headed by an outer bidder in upper stretch, and yielded between horses at the furlong grounds. CRUPI broke slowly, failed to respond to heavy rider encouragement in the early stages culminating with the rider checking for soundness nearing the wire for the first time, raced very far back two wide, cut the gap on the rest of the field in upper stretch, and rallied greenly between horses leaving the three sixteenths pole. CURLY JACK bumped with an outer rival at the start, raced in midpack along the inside, pursued two wide and between horses around the far turn, chased in the four path entering the lane, and faded through the final furlong. VICTORY FORMATION stalked three wide, but was outmoved for show by an inner rival into the far turn, chased from the four path around that bend, and weakened. SHAQ DIESEL stalked along the inside, chased under urging around the far turn, vacated the rail at the three sixteenths pole, and weakened between horses. SILVER HEIST lacked speed three wide, and faded. PRIVATE CREED tracked four wide, but gave way in the six path and between horses around the far turn. QUIET AS MIDNIGHT showed little. DETERMINEDLY set the pace along the inside under steady coaxing, dueled around the far turn, caved entering the lane, and was eased through the final furlong.
